-- Regression: in-place AST node reinterpretation for enum variant resolution.
--
-- **Motivating Incident.** Phase 65 AUDIT-01 ranks 7 and 8 flagged
-- src/analyzer/resolve.c lines 678 and 684 where Iron_EnumConstruct
-- nodes were reinterpreted in place as Iron_MethodCallExpr or
-- Iron_FieldAccess by casting a pointer and overwriting fields. The
-- reinterpret branch fires whenever the parser's uppercase heuristic
-- misidentifies a module static call like `Time.Timer(1.0)` or a module
-- constant like `Log.DEBUG` as an enum construct — resolve then has to
-- rewrite the node into the correct expression kind. The in-place
-- reinterpret was layout-dependent UB: if Iron_EnumConstruct,
-- Iron_MethodCallExpr, or Iron_FieldAccess gained or lost fields, the
-- overwrite would silently corrupt memory in unrelated downstream code
-- paths.
--
-- **Layout Diagram.**
--   Iron_EnumConstruct:  [span][kind][resolved_type][enum_name][variant_name][args][arg_count]
--   Iron_MethodCallExpr: [span][kind][resolved_type][object][method][args][arg_count]
--   Iron_FieldAccess:    [span][kind][resolved_type][object][field]
--
--   The three types share the first three fields (the expression prefix
--   enforced by PROT-01 _Static_assert) but diverge immediately after.
--   Old code wrote enum_name and variant_name at the MethodCallExpr
--   object/method offsets or the FieldAccess object/field offsets —
--   which happened to work only because the surface field types (both
--   pointers) coincided at those positions.
--
-- **Fix Summary.** resolve.c now allocates a fresh Iron_MethodCallExpr
-- or Iron_FieldAccess node via iron_arena_alloc, populates it with the
-- correct fields, and copies the fresh layout over the Iron_EnumConstruct
-- storage (preserving the upstream parent pointer). Size fit is
-- enforced by two `_Static_assert(sizeof(Iron_MethodCallExpr) <=
-- sizeof(Iron_EnumConstruct), ...)` style guards so a future struct-size
-- regression fails the build immediately. IRON_NODE_ASSERT_KIND confirms
-- the pre-cast invariant on `ec`. PROT-04, Phase 66 Plan 03.
--
-- **Severity.** H. Affects every reference to an enum variant in user
-- code: the legitimate enum-variant path flows through the same resolve
-- handler, and this regression fixture exercises both the
-- parameterless (FieldAccess rewrite) and parameterized (MethodCall
-- rewrite) code paths end-to-end.

enum Shape {
  Circle(Int),
  Square,
  Rect(Int, Int),
}

func Shape.area() -> Int {
  match self {
    Shape.Circle(r) -> return r * r
    Shape.Square -> return 16
    Shape.Rect(w, h) -> return w * h
  }
  return 0
}

func main() {
    val c = Shape.Circle(5)        -- exercises the parameterized path
    val sq = Shape.Square          -- exercises the parameterless path
    val r = Shape.Rect(3, 4)
    println("{c.area()}")
    println("{sq.area()}")
    println("{r.area()}")
}
